The quiz, which will be held in August, is open to all high schools in Pretoria. Each school is permitted two teams made up of four pupils up to Grade 11. Questions on current affairs, business, sport and entertainment will be taken from reports in the Pretoria News. The winning school will win R20000, and a bursary worth R75000. Each team member and coach will win R2000. The runner-up school will win R10000 and each team member and the coach will win R1000. The winning Pretoria team will go through to the national final in Sandton in September. To enter e-mail pnquiz@inl.co.za